        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "Currently, there is no way to define the position of FormLabels when elements are rendered in a collection or row.  This is particularly relevant to checkbox, multiCheckbox and radio fields.  By default, checkbox, multiCheckbox, and radio elements should append their label.  Regardless, a '{{label_position}}' configuration option should be available and recognized by the FormCollection and FormRow helpers.\r\n\r\n{code}\r\n\/\/ inside Controller ...\r\n$form->add(array(\r\n   \"name\" => \"remember\",\r\n   \"type\" => \"Zend\\Form\\Element\\Checkbox\",\r\n   \"options\" => array(\r\n      \"label\" => \"Remember Me\",\r\n      \"label_position\" => \"append\",\r\n   ),\r\n));\r\n{code}"
        },
