        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/51812",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bakura",
                        "name": "bakura",
                        "displayName": "Michael Gallego",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "This is a good idea. I'll make a fix tomorrow for that.\r\n\r\nEDIT : the only problem I can see is that this thing is relative to FormRow helper, so this means we are going to introduce something into the base Element that is used only by the FormRow helper. I'll talk to Matthew and cgmartin about that :).",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bakura",
                        "name": "bakura",
                        "displayName": "Michael Gallego",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2012-09-05T21:51:13.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2012-09-05T21:52:59.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/51813",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=cgmartin",
                        "name": "cgmartin",
                        "displayName": "Chris Martin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "We already have the label attributes attached to the base Element, so makes sense to me to be able to set label options on it as well. \r\n\r\nWould it also be helpful to attach the FormElementError attributes (and options?) to the base Element? We run into the same kinds of limitations with rendering the errors as we do with the labels, in the context of FormRow.\r\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=cgmartin",
                        "name": "cgmartin",
                        "displayName": "Chris Martin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2012-09-05T22:03:17.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2012-09-05T22:03:17.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/51817",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bokgc",
                        "name": "bokgc",
                        "displayName": "George Cooksey",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "My main goals for this in every context are:\r\n1. Default (appended) rendering with no configuration for radio\/checkbox elements\r\n2. Custom rendering via configuration\r\n\r\nI also agree with Chris' suggestion regarding errors.\r\n\r\nThe bottom line is that these elements should not be handled like other inputs when rendered.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bokgc",
                        "name": "bokgc",
                        "displayName": "George Cooksey",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2012-09-06T03:40:34.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2012-09-06T03:40:34.000+0000"
                },
